# AI Engineering Framework

Project instructions are canonical in `.ai-engineering/`.

## Skills & Agents

- Skills: `.ai-engineering/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (35 skills, flat layout)
- Agents: `.ai-engineering/agents/<name>.md` (7 agents: plan, execute, build, scan, release, write, observe)

## Plan/Execute Flow (Spec-as-Gate)

When the user says `/ai-plan`:

1. Read `.ai-engineering/agents/plan.md` and follow its behavior.
2. Analyze the request: read code, discover requirements, assess risk.
3. Produce the spec as **text in the conversation** — do NOT write files directly.
4. Persist via CLI: `cat <<'EOF' | ai-eng spec save --title "..." --pipeline standard --size M`
5. STOP and wait for the user to invoke `/ai-execute`.

When the user says `/ai-execute`:

1. Read `.ai-engineering/agents/execute.md` and follow its behavior.
2. Read the active spec from `.ai-engineering/context/specs/_active.md`.
3. Execute tasks phase by phase per the plan.

## Command Contract

- `/ai-plan` — plan + spec creation (STOPS before execution)
- `/ai-execute` — read spec, dispatch implementation
- `/ai-commit` — stage + commit + push
- `/ai-pr` — stage + commit + push + PR

## Quality & Security

- Coverage 80%, duplication ≤3%, cyclomatic ≤10
- Zero medium/high/critical findings, zero leaks
- Run `ruff check` and `ruff format` before committing
